Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.719
&gt;&gt; Picasa is free software from Google that
helps you manage your digital photo collection.

00:00:08.719 --> 00:00:13.990
Using Picasa on your PC, you can organize
and view all your photos in one place.

00:00:13.990 --> 00:00:18.500
Edit your pictures to perfection and get creative
with your favorite photos-- making beautiful

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:26.330
photo collages, video slideshows, prints,
wallpapers, and more.

00:00:26.330 --> 00:00:29.930
Managing your photo collection should be easy
not difficult.

00:00:29.930 --> 00:00:35.370
When you launch the new Picasa 3, you'll immediately
see all the photos on your PC's hard drive

00:00:35.370 --> 00:00:40.120
organized by folder and date.
Adding new photos is as simple as attaching

00:00:40.120 --> 00:00:46.170
a camera and clicking the "Import" button.
You can also create virtual photo albums to

00:00:46.170 --> 00:00:49.500
quickly group together photos for viewing
or sharing.

00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:54.260
Add tags and stars to your standout photos
to easily search and show off your photo collection's

00:00:54.260 --> 00:00:58.070
finest.
The updated interface in Picasa 3 includes

00:00:58.070 --> 00:01:02.579
new controls at the album level.
To help you quickly play a full screen slideshow,

00:01:02.579 --> 00:01:07.040
create collages, movies, and CDs, and manage
online sharing in sync.

00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:13.680
Of course, other common actions that you care
about-- like printing photos or uploading

00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:18.360
albums to share online-- remain as easy as
ever, accessible via the prominent buttons

00:01:18.360 --> 00:01:23.000
in your photos library.
Everybody wants their pictures to look great,

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:28.030
and Picasa 3 has been designed to make great-looking
pictures available to everybody.

00:01:28.030 --> 00:01:32.900
Just double-click any photo to zoom in on
the picture and reveal Picasa's easy-to-use

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:38.619
editing controls, which span basic fixes,
fine tuning, and special effects.

00:01:38.619 --> 00:01:43.920
The "Basic Fixes" tab helps you quickly implement
the most important edits with minimal efforts.

00:01:43.920 --> 00:01:48.720
You can crop and straighten, or adjust color,
contrast, and lighting.

00:01:48.720 --> 00:01:52.950
There's even an "I'm Feeling Lucky" button
that automatically adjusts many settings at

00:01:52.950 --> 00:01:58.020
once to enhance your photo.
Editing features in Picasa are nondestructive.

00:01:58.020 --> 00:02:02.130
You can always revert to your original photo
if you want.

00:02:02.130 --> 00:02:07.049
Brand new in Picasa 3 is a text tool that
lets you add text to any picture.

00:02:07.049 --> 00:02:11.700
Complete with intuitive layout and formatting
controls to help you get perfect results.

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:16.650
Just type some text, drag into position, and
adjust to your liking.

00:02:16.650 --> 00:02:20.860
Also new is a powerful retouching tool to
help you edit like a pro.

00:02:20.860 --> 00:02:24.130
It's an easy way to fix minor blemishes and
other distractions.

00:02:24.130 --> 00:02:28.170
No airbrushing skills required.
We've made many other improvements to the

00:02:28.170 --> 00:02:33.709
powerful and accessible editing features found
in earlier versions of Picasa.

00:02:33.709 --> 00:02:36.890
Red eye fixes, for example, require less work
that ever.

00:02:36.890 --> 00:02:42.099
Now, just press the "Red Eye" button "Basic
Fixes" tab and watch Picasa automatically

00:02:42.099 --> 00:02:47.900
locate and correct the problem.
You'll also notice smarter crop suggestions,

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.569
which are based on the composition of your
photograph.

00:02:50.569 --> 00:02:55.099
Access the "Crop" button, select your choice
of dimension and then get to cropping.

00:02:55.099 --> 00:02:59.260
You can always preview to get a sneak peak
before applying changes.

00:02:59.260 --> 00:03:02.550
Sharing is now more streamlined and faster
than before.

00:03:02.550 --> 00:03:07.739
Click the "Share" button on any album to immediately
upload that album to Picasa web albums and

00:03:07.739 --> 00:03:13.349
let friends know that you've posted new pictures.
Alternatively, select any group of pictures

00:03:13.349 --> 00:03:16.940
and click the "Upload" button.
You control whether your online albums are

00:03:16.940 --> 00:03:22.410
public and searchable or kept at an unlisted
address.

00:03:22.410 --> 00:03:26.849
Web albums can automatically be kept in sync
with the photos on your PC.

00:03:26.849 --> 00:03:31.190
Just enable the "Sync to Web" toggle on any
album in Picasa 3.

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:35.489
After sync is enabled on an album, any photo
fixes or album additions you make on your

00:03:35.489 --> 00:03:40.540
PC will be automatically be uploaded to Picasa
web albums, giving you one less thing to worry

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:44.070
about.
Apart from helping you organize, edit, and

00:03:44.070 --> 00:03:48.879
share your photos, Picasa 3 also introduces
new ways for you to get creative and have

00:03:48.879 --> 00:03:53.250
more fun with your digital camera.
The collage tool, for example, has been greatly

00:03:53.250 --> 00:03:57.810
enhanced and gives you several different collage
types and total artistic freedom over layout

00:03:57.810 --> 00:04:02.560
and content.
To get started, just select a folder or album,

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:07.930
then click the "Create Photo Collage" button.
Changing the layout is easy.

00:04:07.930 --> 00:04:12.209
After customizing your collage, you can use
it as a desktop wallpaper or print at high

00:04:12.209 --> 00:04:16.659
resolution.
Ever take movies with your digital camera?

00:04:16.659 --> 00:04:21.349
Picasa 3 now includes a simple and straightforward
movie maker, so you can create short movies

00:04:21.349 --> 00:04:26.259
featuring your videos, photos, and music,
and easily share them on YouTube.

00:04:26.259 --> 00:04:31.289
Getting started is as easy as selecting an
album and clicking the "Create Movie Presentation"

00:04:31.289 --> 00:04:34.310
button.
Start having fun by adding text, altering

00:04:34.310 --> 00:04:37.830
transition styles, and choosing the right
tunes to match the mood.

00:04:37.830 --> 00:04:42.610
When you are satisfied, click the "Create
Movie" button and Picasa 3 will go to work

00:04:42.610 --> 00:04:46.210
rendering your video.
Once it's done, you can use the YouTube button

00:04:46.210 --> 00:04:49.979
to share with friends or the whole world.
These are just some of the new features in

00:04:49.979 --> 00:04:53.669
the latest version of Picasa.
And there's plenty more, from new slideshow

00:04:53.669 --> 00:04:58.470
transitions to better tagging.
To download Picasa 3 for your own PC, or learn

00:04:58.470 --> 00:05:02.289
more about Picasa web albums, visit picasa.google.com.

